Problem: Valid Parentheses
Topic: Stack, Strings
Difficulty: Easy

Approach:
Use a stack to store opening brackets. For each closing bracket, check if it matches the top of the stack. If it matches, pop; otherwise return false. At the end, the stack should be empty.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(n)

Code:
class Solution {
public:
    bool isValid(string s) {
        stack<char> st;
        for(char c:s){
            if(c=='(' || c=='[' || c=='{'){
                st.push(c);
            }
            else{
                if(st.empty()){
                    return false;
                }
                char top=st.top();
                if((c==')' && top=='(') ||
                  (c==']' && top=='[') ||
                  (c=='}' && top=='{') ){
                    st.pop();
                  }
                  else{
                    return false;
                  }
            }
        }
        return st.empty();
    }
};
